placenta?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aromatase","Sulfatase","16 alpha-hydroxylase","17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase","3 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe placenta and foetus work together in steroid hormone synthesis during pregnancy through a process called the foetal-placental unit. The placenta contains \u003Cstrong\u003Earomatase\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Esulfatase\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003E17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E, but lacks \u003Cstrong\u003E16 alpha-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E. This enzyme is present in the foetal liver and is crucial for the production of oestriol. The foetus also contains \u003Cstrong\u003E3 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis arrangement necessitates cooperation between foetal and placental tissues for complete steroid hormone synthesis. The foetus produces precursors using 16 alpha-hydroxylase, which are then converted to active hormones by placental enzymes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The placenta lacks 16 alpha-hydroxylase, requiring foetal-placental cooperation for oestrogen synthesis","The placenta contains aromatase, sulfatase, and 17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase for steroid hormone production","Foetal-placental cooperation is essential for complete steroid hormone synthesis during pregnancy"],"references":["Napso T, Yong HEJ, Lopez-Tello J, Sferruzzi-Perri AN. The Role of Placental Hormones in Mediating Maternal Adaptations to Support Pregnancy and Lactation. Front Physiol. 2018 Aug 17;9:1091. doi: 10.3389/fphys.2018.01091. PMID: 30174608; PMCID: PMC6108594","Newbern D, Freemark M. Placental hormones and the control of maternal metabolism and fetal growth. Curr Opin Endocrinol Diabetes Obes. 2011 Dec;18(6):409-16. doi: 10.1097/MED.0b013e32834c800d. PMID: 21986512","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57524"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15893"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57524","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57524"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:08:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:10:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8584"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72054"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"3618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3618"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Placental function","sy